{
  "stem": "19923.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he begged to go with him, to go with him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my father said no.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when-- when they got to the police station, he, my father, turned to Joe and said, you're now the head of the family.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Make sure everybody gets taken care of.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And Joe was only 10 years old.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father and my uncle were sent by a freight train to Germany-- to Poland, and that was the last time I ever saw my father, in Kristallnacht, 1938.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I'm not sure the exact date, November 8, 9, or 10, 1938, and that's my last recollection of ever seeing my father.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And after that, of course, once my father and my uncle were deported-- I might just add at this point how Uncle Charles got to London.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He tells the story now that for three days they were in no man's land between Poland and Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the Germans had kicked out these people, and Poland didn't know what to do with them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So after three days, the Polish government decided to let them in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, before the Germans let them off the train, they had them all line up, all in front of the train.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the Gestapo, with the dogs, German shepherd dogs, just like you've seen in the movies, marched all along the line and asked everyone, everyone, how much money did you bring with you?",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if anyone said they brought more than 10 marks, they were beaten on the spot, mercifully beaten on the-- mercifully-- not-- that is mercilessly beaten on the spot with truncheons, and the dogs set upon them.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And before leaving, Uncle Charles had two 250-note German marks.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
